id: hac-r4e3
title: Enforce erasable zero-escape TypeScript and complete source docstrings
description: "Remove explicit any and dynamic imports, inline trivial one-use helpers, verify external API types from installed packages, prohibit non-erasable syntax, and require high-quality documentation coverage for every source file and public contract."
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[4]: docstrings,eslint,type-safety,typescript
created_at: "2026-07-21T19:13:47.535Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-21T20:37:15.768Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-21T20:37:14.862Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 720
acceptance_criteria: No explicit any or dynamic import remains in src; erasable-only TypeScript rules are mandatory; every source file and exported API has a meaningful JSDoc contract; automated lint/doc coverage gates report 100%; no trivial one-call helper remains
definition_of_ready: Source pattern inventory and installed dependency types reviewed
value: Makes implementation intent and type contracts inspectable by maintainers and agents
impact: Prevents unsafe escape hatches and undocumented behavior from entering production
outcome: "Strict, fully documented, erasable TypeScript across the source tree"
why_now: The current source contains explicit any and seven dynamic import sites and has no enforced doc coverage
parent: hac-n0ix
reviewer: unbraind
risk: high
confidence: high
release: 2026.7.22
resolution: "Enabled zero-explicit-any, no dynamic or inline imports, erasable-only syntax, and a deterministic 115/115 source docstring gate while removing trivial redundant branches."
expected_result: "All source is type-safe, erasable, documented, lint-clean, and free of trivial one-use wrappers introduced by this work."
actual_result: Typecheck and ESLint pass; docstring coverage is 115/115; all source remains under 300 code lines; full behavioral coverage is 100%.
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T19:13:56.436Z",codex-root,"Initial source inventory found explicit any in src/utils/exit.ts and src/api/system.ts plus dynamic imports in cli-config, extended, settings-wizard, services, and lists. Installed Undici types will be used for the multipart body instead of a guessed cast."
  "2026-07-21T19:19:12.559Z",codex-root,"2026-07-21 strict scan: bun typecheck passes with erasableSyntaxOnly; source and test scans now contain no explicit any casts/types or dynamic import expressions after replacing formatter fixtures with exact HA types and the fs mock with a static module mock."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T20:37:13.023Z",codex-root,Erasable TypeScript enforcement is most reliable as a lint contract paired with installed-package type inspection; branch coverage also exposed redundant defaults whose removal simplified runtime semantics.
